OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAnother largely dry day with
OL,6,Fhazy sunshine. After a chilly start,
OL,7,Fit will warm up through the day,
OL,8,Fthough still holding onto brisk winds
OL,9,Fearly on.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA clear night with gusty
OL,12,Fwinds to start with but easing through
OL,13,Fthe night. Spots of rain in the far
OL,14,Fsouthwest. Staying mild with most
OL,15,Fplaces staying in double figures.
OL,16,
OL,17,CFriday:FA sunny start in the east but
OL,18,Fmore cloud in the west. Some brighter
OL,19,Fspells develop later with the odd
OL,20,Fisolated shower. Feeling very warm in
OL,21,Fthe east.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
